fields.name: Hartwood Revival Vibrato Semi Acoustic Guitar, Cherry Red
fields.description: The Hartwood Revival Semi Acoustic will bring a classic edge to your sound. Its iconic semi acoustic style is matched with an authentic feel and a warm, traditional tone. This model has been designed to make your sound stand out. With a classic neck and bridge humbucker configuration and parallel tonebar bracing, this guitar produces a striking tone that will cut through the mix. It also delivers dynamic tonal possibilities thanks to a rich basswood body.

fields.name: Fender Custom Shop CuNiFe Telecaster Custom, Aged Chartreuse Sparkle
fields.description: The Fender Custom Shop CuNiFe Telecaster revives a classic tone, encompassing all the traditional Fender characteristics that made the Telecaster so iconic - this guitar brings them into the modern era. Upholding Fender Custom Shop's prestige, this Telecaster is built to a level of excellence and craftsmanship only achievable with the utmost delicacy.

fields.name: PRS Private Stock, Chesapeake Bay Bridge #PS9620
fields.description: The PRS Ltd Edition Private Stock is the best of the best. All the premium woods which make it up have been hand selected from PRS's legendary Private Stock vault, which contains the finest woods you'll ever lay eyes on. It all starts with the curly maple which has been used for the top of this guitar. Rare and beautiful, this luscious wood offers incredible grain patterns which accentuate the pristine, professional-grade finish. And African ribbon mahogany makes up the back, providing a solid, seamless foundation for this guitar's looks and tone. This is far more than just a guitar - it's a piece of art.

fields.name: Ibanez PIA3761, Stallion White
fields.description: Unrivalled performance. Visionary style. A masterclass in both. To quote Steve Vai, the Ibanez PIA3761 is 'one of the best instruments in the universe.' Alongside breath taking good looks, this legendary axe gives you full access to fierce tonal textures, going from gritty bite to vicious crunch with just pick attack alone. Join one of the biggest guitar heroes on the planet, and unlock infinite creative freedom.

fields.name: EVH Striped Frankie, Red/White/Black
fields.description: Globally recognised. Universally adored. You don't need to be a historian to know that the EVH Striped Frankie is a cultural icon. Built to recreate Eddie Van Halen's legendary Frankenstein Stratocaster, this statement piece not only looks the part, but sounds fierce and phenomenal – just like the original. Unlock Van Halen's unorthodox playing style and engineering ingenuity. This is the ultimate guitar for tone, dependability, and style.

fields.name: Gibson Les Paul Standard 60s, Iced Tea
fields.description: Fall in love with tone. A Gibson Les Paul Standard '60s is your ticket to the iconic sounds of classic Les Pauls. Celebrated all over the world as one of the best guitars of all time, the Les Paul Standard has been used by countless legendary guitarists in a wide range of genres. This guitar provides a truly authentic '60s Gibson experience, perfectly encapsulating the look, feel, and most importantly, sound of a classic '60s Les Paul Standard.

fields.name: Gibson Les Paul Custom, Ebony
fields.description: ...and on the seventh day, Gibson created yet another masterpiece. There's a reason why some of the most influential and iconic artists in music history swear by the Gibson Custom Les Paul. Classic, elegant, and versatile. This instrument handles any genre. From the roots of reggae to classic rock - nothing is off limits. The 490R and 498T humbuckers are perfect for handling any genre you're into.

fields.name: Fender Player Telecaster MN, Tidepool
fields.description: Pristine performance. Sensational sound. The Fender Player Telecaster MN presents one of Fender's most treasured models with a design that excels on the modern stage. Featuring a pair of Alnico 5 single-coil pickups, a tone of scintillating vintage quality ripples through the mix with each note you play. All the snap, bite, and character of a classic Tele, more accessible than ever before.

fields.name: Dean ML Select Floyd Quilt Top, Trans Brazilia
fields.description: Sleek, sharp, superior. The Dean ML Select is the metalhead's dream, with a host of high quality features giving it the ability to roar with tonal aggression. If you like to make a lot of high gain noise on your guitar, then you'll instantly fall in love with the heavy, saturated sounds this musical machine is capable of producing. Two Seymour Duncan pickups in the neck and bridge help create a tone with bite, punch, and resounding aggression, which will send shivers down your spine.

fields.name: Epiphone Slash Les Paul, Anaconda Burst
fields.description: The Epiphone Slash Les Paul is the latest iteration of Slash's iconic line of signature guitars. Synonymous with the single cutaway design of Les Pauls, the latest models have finishes based on Slash's pet snakes for a truly distinctive aesthetic. The Custom ProBucker pickups are replica's of Gibson's Custom BurstBuckers for premium performance, instantly delivering Slash's signature tones

fields.name: Dean Z X Floyd, Black Satin
fields.description: Careful, they're hot! The duo of DMT Design humbuckers loaded into this guitar scream with power. Offering a tight, dynamic tone and mountains of energy, they'll blast your riffs out like bullets. The bridge pickup is perfect for rhythm playing, giving your notes pronounced bite and plenty of definition. Switch to the neck pickup for sensational, saturated lead tone. It gives your licks a rich, beefy voicing which makes each note glisten with saturation. Get rocking.

fields.name: Ibanez RG421MSP, Turquoise Sparkle
fields.description: The Ibanez RG421MSP summons progressive greatness from all the elements. Designed to harness your aggression, you can unleash your destructive musical storm without worrying about whether your axe can handle it. The Rocky of the guitar world. The Wizard III maple neck is thin, flat and fast, and yet, will stay sturdy and take a beating like a champ.

fields.name: PRS SE Standard 24, Translucent Blue
fields.description: Classic design with enhanced playability. That is exactly what the PRS SE Standard 24 offers. Based on the Custom 24 model, it features the same dynamic 85/15 S pickups and sturdy hardware that provide firm tuning stability. Lose yourself in those magnificent vibrato techniques and perform confidently knowing your strings will return to pitch.

fields.name: Gretsch G2410TG Streamliner Hollow SC, Village Amber
fields.description: A new take on a legendary tone... that is exactly what the Broad'Tron BT-2S humbuckers provide. Specifically designed for the Streamliner, they harness the same power as the renowned Broad'Trons but offer a much tighter bass tone and pronounced midrange. Immerse yourself in gleaming highs and explore the wonders of such a consistent, dynamic tone. They are perfect for modern players as they can meet every single demand and always sound fantastic.

fields.name: SubZero Paradigm Electric Guitar, Black Burl Burst
fields.description: Perform with confidence. The Paradigm's fretboard is crowned with 24 frets, and rock-solid locking tuners ensure your guitar remains in perfect pitch throughout bends and pick scrapes alike. Additionally, by reducing string slippage and the number of string winds required to reach your pitch, sustain and string life are improved. Ideal for gigging and studio performances.

fields.name: Fender Acoustasonic Player Telecaster, Butterscotch Blonde
fields.description: The Fender Acoustasonic Player Telecaster is an evolution of Fender's fantastic Acoustasonic platform. This acoustic-electric guitar offers a unique voice that emits an abundance of personality. Switch efficiently between electric and acoustic tones, with a designated three-way switch, allowing you to shape the guitar's sound to fit your performance. Designed with a mahogany body, the guitar produces a rich, warm, full-bodied tone, with a delicate yet distinct character

fields.name: Fender PM-2 Parlor Mahogany Acoustic, Natural
fields.description: Fender have birthed an authentic parlour acoustic with a head-turning tone. This PM-2 Parlor develops more sonic character, the more you play. An instrument that continues to sonically grow, and sound better with age. Crafted with a meticulous attention to detail to deliver a stunning sound with a premium vibe.

fields.name: Dean Exhibition Koa Electro Acoustic
fields.description: The Dean Exhibition Koa features a solid koa top, which not only provides an exceptionally striking visual but also delivers a bright and punchy tonality. It also offers a sweet, warmer, and full toned voice as the koa matures. Its top is contrasted beautifully by its mahogany back and sides, as it produces a more focused, woody, punchy mid-range, thick well-defined tone with plenty of depth and complexity that will please most playing styles.

fields.name: Hartwood Sonata-FX Thinline Electro-Acoustic Guitar, Sunburst
fields.description: The Hartwood Sonata-FX Thinline Electro-Acoustic Guitar offers a comprehensive all-in-one solution to practice, performance, and writing. Comprised of a premium selection of tonewoods, the Sonata-FX Thinline includes a solid sitka spruce top, flamed maple sides, as well as a maple neck, all of which complement one another, guaranteeing a full-frequency, responsive playing experience.

fields.name: Yamaha F370 Acoustic, Black
fields.description: A classic. And sometimes, true tradition is what you really need. So this Yamaha F370 Acoustic brings you just that. An authentic instrument reminiscent of traditional acoustic guitars from days gone by. And, it comes packed with world renowned Yamaha quality.

fields.name: Martin SC-13E Electro Acoustic, Natural
fields.description: Game-changing. Are you ready for an instrument you'll never live without? Calling all acoustic players, your dream guitar has arrived. And it's here to give you a lifetime of true expression. Birthed for the stage, this Martin SC-13E Electro Acoustic holds all that distinctive, iconic Martin character but with a feel like never before. And a limitless sonic nature. It's time to dig deep into your creativity.

fields.name: Gibson G-00 Generation Acoustic, Natural
fields.description: The Gibson G-00 is brilliantly crafted for practising and ready equipped for stage. Designed with a Gibson player port, a feature that has been refined from a concept first developed in the early 1960s, Gibson's acoustic luthier team have helped deliver a revolutionary new dimension to their sound. Crafted by highly skilled craftspeople in Bozeman, MT, the premium construction makes the acoustic guitar sonically superb.

fields.name: Taylor T5z Classic
fields.description: Create your own unique sound. This stunning instrument from Taylor brings guitarists the best of both worlds. By offering the ability to move between melodic, warm acoustic tones and claasic rock n roll vibes, the Taylor T5z Classic is one of the most versatile and responsive instruments to join your live or recording setup. This distinctive instrument also features a more compact body than the original model, offering comfort and superb playability. A Venetian cutaway also offers added comfort whilst providing easy access to upper frets.

fields.name: Gibson SJ-200 Studio Rosewood, Rosewood Burst
fields.description: Beautiful resonance. Visually stunning. Add yourself to the long line of legends that yield this iconic guitar. The Gibson SJ-200 Studio Rosewood has joined the King of the Flat-Tops as a breath-taking new addition boasting exquisite features. Why tweak perfection? Great question. Adding in an Advanced Response neck profile and slim body depth design, Gibson have made sure that injecting sophistication and personality to your performance has never been so comfortable.

fields.name: Fender Sonoran Mini Acoustic, Mahogany
fields.description: Inviting. Sound that's defined decades of music. Crafted entirely with mahogany, the Sonoran Mini is perfect for any player that adores Fender's Southern Californian history. And it's perfect for a multitude of scenarios. Whether you're on the road, a younger player, new learner, or forever playing outdoors, you deserve a quality tone.

fields.name: Ashdown Saint 5-String Bass RW, Candy Apple Red
fields.description: The Ashdown Saint Bass will ignite your playing with its sparky playability and sublime tone. A pair of P and J Bass style pickups give you a wealth of tonal diversity and flair to play with, letting you write smooth, rich basslines as well as thunderous, pounding riffs. You'll be in awe at their outstanding capabilities, helping bring any amp tone to life.

fields.name: Jackson Spectra Bass SBP V, Cherry Burst
fields.description: Clarity across the spectrum. With a Jackson Pro Spectra V NT in your hands, your basslines will be unstoppable. Its Nordstrand pickups offer superb articulation, meaning they bring out every detail in the notes you're playing. From a crisp, tight, bouncing voicing to deep, warm, lusciously low voicing, you can be sure that they cater to all styles and tones. And with a wealth of further tone-shaping tools, including an active three-band EQ, three-way mid variable switch, and push/pull controls for active/passive voicings

fields.name: Charvel Pro Mod San Dimas JJ V Bass, Candy Apple Red
fields.description: The complete bass guitar. Full-featured, yet uncomplicated, for immediate low-end satisfaction. The Charvel Pro Mod San Dimas JJ V Bass is simply a cut above when it comes to classic bass guitar tones. Its unbeatable quality begins with a pair of DiMarzio pickups, with the J-style model at the neck providing that unmistakable J-bass punch, while its counterpart at the bridge gives a present, driving sound.

fields.name: Fender Player Plus Active Precision Bass MN, Silver Smoke
fields.description: The Fender Player Plus Active Precision Bass MN brings excellent playability, sleek aesthetic, and superb sound in one beast of an instrument. Crafted from alder and adorned with a dazzling 3-ply black pickguard, this bass is truly captivating to look at and even more incredible to play. Waltz seamlessly across the maple fretboard with the maple neck sitting comfortably in your hand - this bass is built for effortless playing.

fields.name: Ibanez EHB1005MS Bass Workshop, Black Flat
fields.description: Superior style. Electric performance. It's time to light up the stage without limitations. The Ibanez EHB1005MS Bass Workshop has all the features you need for liquid fast riffing, lightning energy and experimental play - and you get all this while looking slick. The headless construction offers ultimate comfort and freedom while performing. Nothing can stop you. The balance and lightweight feel mean that you can play for longer so your genius won't be restricted.

fields.name: Fender Aerodyne Jazz Bass, Black
fields.description: It's not a plane. But if it was, it'd be super-fast. As one of Fender's sleekest, slickest basses, the Fender Aerodyne Jazz Bass fires electrifying basslines out at supersonic speed. Precise, high level craftsmanship has gone into every area of its design, and it has been made in japan to an exceptional standard. The split single coil Precision Bass and single coil Jazz Bass duo of pickups really delivers unparalleled tone. Bright, clear, and rich, your sound will be better articulated than ever.

fields.name: Fender Custom Shop Precision Jazz Journey Relic, Aged Candy Apple Red
fields.description: Rarity at your fingertips. Prestige laced through your sound. The Fender Custom Shop Precision Jazz Journey Relic is a divine display of timeless design, combining Precision Bass tone with the sumptuous playability of a Jazz Bass build. A hand-wound '65-'70 Precision Bass pickup delivers a superb vintage tone, encompassing a deliciously defined low range for a brilliantly punchy sound. Vintage hardware then gives us a glimpse into the past and provide a glorious and authentic playing experience.

fields.name: 3 Pack of Bass Guitar Strings
fields.description: String gauge 040-95 - most bass guitars we sell come strung with this gauge as part of the factory setup.

fields.name: Bass Guitar Strings
fields.description: String gauge 040-95 - most bass guitars we sell come strung with this gauge as part of the factory setup.

fields.name: Ernie Ball Regular Slinky 2221 Nickel Guitar Strings 10-46
fields.description: Give your guitar a new lease of life. The Ernie Ball Regular Slinky Nickel Strings promise clear, dynamic sound as well as brilliant robustness. Ernie Ball have set the standard for electric strings, they are iconic and have been used by the likes of Eric Clapton, Slash, and John Mayor. So, you know you can trust in them. Better still, they will arrive to you in Element Shield packaging which protects them against humidity, meaning they are fresh and ready to play.

fields.name: Ernie Ball Power Slinky 2220 Nickel Guitar Strings 11 - 48
fields.description: Give your guitar a new lease of life. The Ernie Ball Power Slinky Nickel Strings promise clear, dynamic sound as well as brilliant robustness. Ernie Ball have set the standard for electric strings, they are iconic and have been used by the likes of Eric Clapton, Slash, and John Mayor. So, you know you can trust in them. Better still, they will arrive to you in Element Shield packaging which protects them against humidity, meaning they are fresh and ready to play.

fields.name: Martin M140 80/20 Bronze Acoustic Strings 12-54
fields.description: The Martin M140 80/20 Bronze Acoustic Strings 012-054 consist of Light gauge 12-16-25-32-42-54. Martin & Co's Traditional flagship line are favoured for their reliability and excellent clarity. The 80/20 Bronze Acoustic Guitar Strings are manufactured to the highest quality, with a tin plated steel core wire and bronze wrap wire, providing exceptional performance and a clear acoustic tone. The Martin Bronze Acoustic Strings consist of 80% copper and 20% zinc, which is a popular combination as they provide a bright and brilliant tone when they are initially put on the guitar. yet they mellow over time.

fields.name: Swiff K8-U Zinc Alloy Ukulele Capo, Brushed Copper
fields.description: The Swiff K8-U Zinc Alloy Ukulele Capo is a reliable capo designed specifically for your ukulele. It features a robust design with quality silicon padding for a top-notch performance. Plus, this high-end design ensures no damage to your instrument's finish too. But that's not all, the precision spring mechanism keeps the K8-U securely fastened to prevent any disruption to the strings while delivering pure sonic goodness, so you can just keep playing your way. And, with a stylish brushed copper finish, this is a capo that'll look superb on stage or whilst filming as well.

fields.name: Deluxe Acoustic/Electric Guitar Capo
fields.description: Capos are used to change the key and pitch of the open strings of a guitar without having to adjust the strings with the tuning keys. This essential accessory has important uses for any style or genre of playing.

fields.name: D'Addario Eclipse Tuner, Purple
fields.description: The D'Addario Eclipse Tuner brings you plenty of features at a great price. Never go out of tune again. Usable with electric, acoustic and bass guitars, the Eclipse tuner has so much utility and it couldn't be easier to work with. Just clip the device to the headstock of your instrument and tune away, the colour screen will assist you in getting the exact pitch you're looking for. In addition to the swivel action and sharp colour, it combines to make an accessory that's incredibly versatile and yet handy for any situation.

fields.name: HT-55 Headstock Chromatic Tuner
fields.description: The HT-55 chromatic tuner is simple to use. By attaching the tuner to the instrument using the high quality clip, the vibration sensor detects the note automatically and shows you the fine tuning to within 5 of a semitone. When the note is perfectly in tune, the display turns green for instant recognition.

fields.name: BOSS TU-3S Chromatic Tuner
fields.description: Every design aspect of the TU-3S has been implemented to deliver the best possible performance and tuning capabilities with everything from a 21-segment LED meter with brightness control for easy monitoring to support for 7-string guitars and 6-string basses. The tuner also features a 'High Brightness' mode which enahcnes the brightness of the meter for low-light coniditions or increased visibility outdoors.

fields.name: Fender Professional 10ft Straight Instrument Cable, White Tweed
fields.description: A premium accessory to take on tour. The Fender Professional 10ft Straight Instrument Cable is a top quality instrument lead that's built to meet all the requirements of the modern touring musician. And top of that list is its ability to communicate your playing clearly and precisely. That's because it's made from high calibre components to ensure you hear everything with clarity.

fields.name: Fender Deluxe 18.6ft Straight/Angle Instrument Cable, Black Tweed
fields.description: A tough, stage-ready cable. Made from the highest quality materials, the Fender Deluxe 18.6ft Straight/Angle Instrument Cable is designed to withstand the rough conditions of touring. The strong braided shielding and woven tweed jacket provide ultimate protection to the internal wiring, making a top-quality instrument lead that you can rely on.

fields.name: Ernie Ball 30ft Straight-Straight Coiled Instrument Cable, Black
fields.description: A durable and flexible cable. The Ernie Ball 30ft Straight-Straight Coiled Instrument Cable, Black is strong thanks to its high-quality design. It's built to last.

fields.name: Venom COBRA-20 Guitar Lead 20ft
fields.description: High-quality cabling for your guitar. The Venom COBRA Guitar Lead is a must-have for performances and studio recording. The oxygen-free design delivers the purest signal integrity, ensuring the best possible sound reproduction. It captures every nuance of your performance without affecting the tonality.

fields.name: Coiled Jack Right Angled Instrument Cable, 1m
fields.description: Quality cable fitted with chrome 1/4 (6.35mm) mono jack plugs

fields.name: Ernie Ball 4235 Ring Slider
fields.description: It rings true. The Ernie Ball 4235 Ring Slider is perfect for all genres of slide guitar. Made from brass, it has machine turned edges for unrivalled smoothness and ease of playing. It's comfy as well as robust – you can use it live in confidence. Make your slide guitar shine like never before.

fields.name: Revv G20 Lunchbox Valve Head w/ Two Notes Cab Emulation
fields.description: Rev up your creativity. The Revv G20 Lunchbox Valve Head w/ Two Notes Cab Emulation really does have it all. Featuring 20W of full tube power, it'll bring the thunder to all live performances - but it's perfect for recording too. Containing a wealth of internal features, including virtual mics, virtual speakers, virtual cabs, EQ, and more, you'll get truly stunning results in any home or studio recording session

fields.name: Marshall ORI50H Origin 50W Valve Head
fields.description: The ORI50H Origin Amp Head is designed to offer an unmistakable Marshall performance and tone, equipped with ECC83 preamp and EL34 power valves to deliver a beautifully rich harmonic content and exceptional tonal quality.

fields.name: Fender Tone Master Twin Reverb
fields.description: This isn't a replica. This is the modern day Twin Reverb. Originating from 1963, the Twin Reverb has powered many iconic performances and inspired generations of musicians. From day one, the Twin Reverb always delivered that power and sonic richness needed for live performance.

fields.name: Roland JC-120 Jazz Chorus Guitar Amplifier
fields.description: In 1975, Roland welcomed the arrival of the first JC-120. A revolution in guitar amplifier technology, the JC-120 Jazz Chorus looked and sounded like no other amp. Thirty years later, the JC-120 remains in high demand by guitarists around the world. Unchanged from its original specification, the JC had attained legendary status by amp connoisseurs the world over.

fields.name: Boss Nextone Artist 80w Guitar Amplifier
fields.description: Tube sounds, modern flexibility. A new concept in tonal versatility. The Boss Nextone Artist 80w Guitar Amplifier gives you all the unique characteristics of 6V6, 6L6, EL84, and EL34 tube amps in one place, letting you experience these signature power stages without the need for multiple amps. Its control panel is fitted with an assortment of controllable parameters and in-built effects. Your creativity won't ever be dampened by the sheer amount of soundscapes you can create.

fields.name: Roland Blues Cube Artist Guitar Amplifier, Cream
fields.description: Warm, bouncy, responsive, dynamic, elastic - these are all terms that guitarists use to describe their favourite tube amps. Thanks to Roland's Tube Logic, these words can be applied to the Blues Cube Artist as well.

fields.name: Vox AC30C2X Custom Combo
fields.description: VOX Custom Series amps offer two channels: Normal and Top-Boost. Each channel is equipped with its own Volume control, and the Top Boost channel offers highly interactive Treble and Bass tone controls. This powerful channel pairing provides an abundance of tone-crafting control, letting you dial in a classic sound that is all your own.

fields.name: Vox AC15C2 Twin Custom Guitar Amplifier
fields.description: Vox have been at the forefront of amplification for over 60 years. This level of experience is truly reflected in the mastery of their craftsmanship. The AC15C2 is no exception, packed with two 12” Celestion G12M speakers, you can hear every frequency emitted allowing each chord to chime with the intended presence and notation

fields.name: Vox AC15C1 Custom Guitar Amp
fields.description: The Vox AC15C1 allows you to dial into a vintage sound that can be made completely your own with its normal and top-boost channels. Each channel is equipped with its very own volume control, and the top-boost channel provides highly interactive treble and bass controls

fields.name: Marshall JVM205C 50W 2x12 Valve Combo
fields.description: The JVM 2 Series features five brand-new, professional, all-valve 100 Watt and 50 Watt 2 channel amps, available in both head and combo formats. Both channels offer three footswitchable modes, effectively giving you six Marshall's in one! Built-in England with pride and armed with 16 controls and six switches, all five JVM2s are easy to understand and are intuitive to use.

fields.name: Marshall 2245 JTM45 Reissue Valve Head
fields.description: You know what it is. It's the Marshall sound. From the very beginnings in 1962 when Jim Marshall created his very first legendary amp, comes a reissue in the form of the Marshall 2245 JTM45 Reissue Valve Head. Meticulously replicating the original Marshall sound, this amp has a GZ34 valve rectifier that works with the ECC83 and 5881 valves to give you the harmonic and unmistakable Marshall tone.

fields.name: SubZero Critical Mass Distortion Pedal
fields.description: With the SubZero Critical Mass Distortion Pedal, the power's very much in your hands. A lot of distortion pedals have one tweakable sound, this is the opposite. Thanks to the responsive nature of the controls there will be nothing stopping you achieving a broad range of distorted tones:

fields.name: Boss DD-8 Digital Delay Pedal
fields.description: For a pedal of such small size, the DD-8 contains a world of possibilities. Taking over from its predecessor, the DD-7, Boss have loaded its fresh design with a bundle of new features fit for the modern stage. Three newly developed delay types mean there are even more ways to innovate your ambient sound.

fields.name: Eventide UltraTap Stompbox
fields.description: The Eventide UltraTap is a unique multi-tap delay pedal that creates rhythmic delays, pad-like volume swells, unique modulation and glitchy reverb all in a compact pedal format. UltraTap's controls allow you to explore new and incidental delay effects. Featuring all the expected controls such as Feedback, Mix and Delay, the UltraTap also has controls for Spread, Slurm and Chop that open up a new world of possibilities.

fields.name: Boss DD-500 Digital Delay Pedal
fields.description: The Boss DD-500 Digital Delay Pedal is an extremely powerful and high-performance delay designed to provide 12 different types of studio quality delay effects in a single robust unit. With everything from 1980s style digital delays to modern reverse delays

fields.name: TC Electronic Flashback Triple Delay
fields.description: A dedicated subdivision knob lets you assign different rhythmic patterns to each delay - everything from dotted eighths to triplets and on to several types of dual delays. Select different subdivision types for each delay, ranging from quarter notes to triplets, and all the way to several kinds of dual delays. Switch between having your delays in series or parallel for lush sonic soundscapes or well defined syncopated echoes.

fields.name: Ibanez TS808 Tube Screamer Overdrive Pro
fields.description: The Ibanez TS808 Tube Screamer Overdrive Pro proves that sometimes you just can't beat the original. A landmark pedal, and one that has rightly cemented its place in musical history on countless recordings and performances- from SRV to John Mayer.

fields.name: JHS Pedals Bonsai 9-Way Overdrive
fields.description: The JHS Pedals Bonsai 9-Way Overdrive embodies the very essence of tubescreamer pedals, equipped with 9 incredibly powerful and unique overdrives for a truly versatile performance.

fields.name: JHS Pedals AT+ Andy Timmons Signature Drive
fields.description: The JHS Pedals AT+ Andy Timmons Signature Drive takes the poplar JHS AT pedal and adds a new independent boost for even more versatile functionality. The original 2016 AT pedal delivered Andy Timmons' signature overdrive sound, characterised in his unmistakable lead and rhythm tones.

fields.name: Strymon TimeLine Delay Pedal
fields.description: The Strymon TimeLine Delay is a guitar pedal that offers an innovative design, coupled with hand crafted delay algorithms and an incredibly high-performance DSP to produce 12 unique delay machines.

fields.name: Dunlop GCB95 CryBaby Wah Pedal
fields.description: The Jim Dunlop GCB95 Original Crybaby Wah Wah pedal has been a true staple of classic rock and blues since the early 60s.

fields.name: Strymon DIG Dual Digital Delay Pedal
fields.description: The Strymon DIG Dual Digital Delay is a guitar pedal that offers a range of unique digital delays to select and shape from - allowing you to find your perfect sound.

fields.name: Dunlop Eddie Van Halen Wah Pedal
fields.description: Make it wail. As this is irresistible Eddie Van Halen wah flavour. Complete with a robust, road-ready design. All oozing from the Dunlop Eddie Van Halen Wah Pedal.

fields.name: Boss DS-1 Distortion Pedal
fields.description: A timeless classic. The Boss DS-1 Distortion Pedal is still going strong 40 years after being introduced, and with good reason. Delivering dirty distortion with more than a hit of grit, all with a stunningly bright tone and it becomes rapidly apparent why Kurt Cobain trusted this pedal to deliver the huge, fuzzy tones that were necessary.

fields.name: SubZero Arctic Fuzz Micro Guitar Pedal
fields.description: The SubZero Arctic Fuzz Micro Guitar Pedal is a perfect accessory for any gigging musician. Featuring high quality construction and a complete analog circuit design, this pedal is easy to use and sounds fantastic.

fields.name: SubZero Slick Lick Vintage Overdrive Pedal
fields.description: The SubZero Slick Lick Vintage Overdrive Pedal is a comprehensive overdrive that can do everything from amp breakup to soaring lead tones, and everything in between.
